# Copy to `.dev.vars` for local `wrangler dev`. NEVER commit `.dev.vars`.
# These are LOCAL-ONLY dev vars. Production secrets live in Worker secrets
# (`wrangler secret put`), never in wrangler.toml [vars] and never in git.

# ─── Salted-IP / cursor / badge HMAC salt ([SECURITY/Opus] "Secrets") ─────────
# Keyed salt for the non-reversible salted-IP hash (BudgetLedger per-visitor windows)
# and for opaque cursor/badge integrity. In PRODUCTION this is a Worker SECRET
# (`wrangler secret put HASH_SALT`), NEVER wrangler.toml [vars] and NEVER git. Locally
# set any >=16-char random value. Missing salt fails closed.
HASH_SALT="local-dev-salt-change-me-0123456789"

# ─── Admin authoring bearer key ([SECURITY/Opus], Phase 1.4) ──────────────────
# Scoped bearer key for CLI suite-publish / baseline-pin. Stored server-side as an
# argon2id hash; this local value is the plaintext key the CLI presents. Unset until
# the admin surface lands. Do NOT reuse across environments.
# ADMIN_BEARER_KEY=""
